objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of daratumumab plus Rd (DRd) over Rd alone in terms of progression-free survival (PFS)

endpoints.name: Progression-free survival
endpoints.text: Progression-free survival (PFS) per International Myeloma Working Group (IMWG) criteria

endpoints.name: MRD Negativity Rate
endpoints.text: MRD negativity rate, defined as the proportion of subjects assessed as MRD negative, at any timepoint after the date of randomization

estimands.name: Primary Efficacy Estimand for PFS
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with multiple myeloma meeting eligibility criteria (ITT population) Summary measure: Hazard ratio.

intercurrentEvents.name: Discontinuation of study treatment
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject discontinues study treatment for reasons other than disease progression

intercurrentEvents.name: Death
intercurrentEvents.text: Death due to any cause prior to disease progression

estimands.treatment: Daratumumab plus Lenalidomide and Dexamethasone (DRd) vs Lenalidomide and Dexamethasone (Rd)
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with multiple myeloma meeting eligibility criteria (ITT population)

estimands.name: Overall Survival Estimand
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with multiple myeloma meeting eligibility criteria (ITT population) Summary measure: Hazard ratio.

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment Switching (Crossover)
intercurrentEvents.text: Subjects in Arm A (Rd) receiving daratumumab after confirmed disease progression

estimands.treatment: Daratumumab plus Lenalidomide and Dexamethasone (DRd) vs Lenalidomide and Dexamethasone (Rd)
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with multiple myeloma meeting eligibility criteria (ITT population)

estimands.name: MRD Negativity Rate Estimand
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with multiple myeloma meeting eligibility criteria (ITT population) Summary measure: Odds ratio.

intercurrentEvents.name: Death or Disease Progression
intercurrentEvents.text: Death or disease progression before achieving MRD negativity

estimands.treatment: Daratumumab plus Lenalidomide and Dexamethasone (DRd) vs Lenalidomide and Dexamethasone (Rd)
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with multiple myeloma meeting eligibility criteria (ITT population)
estimands.variableOfInterest: MRD negativity rate at any timepoint after randomization

estimands.name: Time to Response Estimand
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with multiple myeloma meeting eligibility criteria (ITT population) Summary measure: Median time to response.

intercurrentEvents.name: Death without response
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject dies before achieving a response

estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with multiple myeloma meeting eligibility criteria (ITT population)

estimands.populationSummary: Subjects who achieved MRD negativity Summary measure: Median duration.

intercurrentEvents.text: Subject loses MRD negative status or dies
